external_knowledge:
- "journey" metaphorically represents the project lifecycle;
- "unique identifiers" and "names" refer to project_id and project_name;
- "tasks they carry within their sails" represents the total tasks associated with each project;
- "currently afloat" refers to active tasks;
- "safely docked" signifies completed tasks.

- Position levels refer to the hierarchical levels within the company (e.g., top-level management, middle management, regular employees); 
- The amount of work refers to the total number of tasks in the department;
- Typical time spent on tasks refers to the average hours dedicated to completing tasks within the department.

sql:
SELECT task_subject, estimated_hours
FROM tasks
WHERE estimated_hours > (SELECT AVG(estimated_hours) FROM tasks);

